​​# I-CAMS Frontend Environment Configuration

## Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the `frontend/` directory with the following variables:

```env
# Application
REACT_APP_NAME=I-CAMS
REACT_APP_VERSION=1.0.0
REACT_APP_ENVIRONMENT=development

# API Configuration
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
REACT_APP_API_TIMEOUT=30000

# Authentication
REACT_APP_SESSION_TIMEOUT=1800000
REACT_APP_TOKEN_NAME=icams_auth_token

# Features
REACT_APP_ENABLE_NOTIFICATIONS=true
REACT_APP_ENABLE_MESSAGING=true
REACT_APP_ENABLE_CHARTS=true

# Analytics (Optional)
REACT_APP_ANALYTICS_ID=your_analytics_id

# Feature Flags
REACT_APP_FEATURE_HEALTH_TRENDS=true
REACT_APP_FEATURE_PATIENT_QUEUE=true
REACT_APP_FEATURE_SECURE_MESSAGING=true
```

## Development Environment

```env
REACT_APP_ENVIRONMENT=development
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
REACT_APP_DEBUG=true
```

## Production Environment

Create a `.env.production` file:

```env
REACT_APP_ENVIRONMENT=production
REACT_APP_API_URL=https://api.icams.example.com/api
REACT_APP_DEBUG=false
```

## Security Notes

- Never commit `.env` files to version control
- Store sensitive keys on the server/environment
- Rotate tokens regularly
- Use HTTPS in production
- Enable CORS properly on backend

## Accessing Environment Variables

```javascript
const apiUrl = process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL;
const isDevelopment = process.env.REACT_APP_ENVIRONMENT === 'development';
```
